t as the biggest complement. In contrast, this book (as we were warned repeatedly) was also a tearjerker.*mini-spoiler, but not really - it brushes upon how much/little sex there is in this book. The rest of the review is completely spoiler free!*This book had a slow burn, and I was actually surprised by the fact that there was only one sex scene, and it took place fairly close to the end. I have to confess I was expecting things to heat up a lot quicker, but that was admittedly before I really got into the book and really grasped the character dynamics.CJ was the adorable. &#62;Dan with CJ&#60; made my ovaries explode. I practically awwwh-ing in any scene they were together.One of my favorite scenes was when Dan was helping Gen out when CJ was sick and she was a train wreck. He took CJ off her hands for a bit so she could shower and take a nap. She was listening to them through the baby monitor. Read this scene and feel your ovaries go boom (if you have them, that is. You could be equipped with cojones for all I know) ;)All in all it was a very entertaining read, and I was laughing out loud several times. It was hilariously written. I think H.M. Ward and Stacey Mosteller was a great match!I had a couple of peeves, which is why I&#8217;m settling on 4.5 stars for this book. My only real complaint is that I wished the ending were a little more powerful. The few other peeves I had were not that significant overall, but if you are interested to see what they are you can do so here: bit.ly/1tpKzhW", "overall": 5.0, "summary": "H.M. Ward teams up with Stacey Mosteller for emotional contemporary romance - spoiler free!", "unixReviewTime": 1405900800, "reviewTime": "07 21, 2014"}
